ABUJA – Troops of 223 Battalion, operating under Sector 1 of Joint Task Force, North West Operations Hadarin Daji, have rescued 24 kidnap victims, including a child, after a shootout with notorious bandits at Kabugu Lamba. Kabugu Lamba is said to be an abandoned village in Maru Local Government Area of Zamfara state, North West Nigeria. According to Brigadier General Onyema Nwachuku, Director Army Public Relations, “The gallant troops led by the Commanding Officer of the Battalion, stalked and swooped on the bandits, annihilating four of them in a ferocious firefight that ensued. “The victims, including a minor, nine females and 14 males have been extricated and evacuated from the kidnappers’ hideout by the troops.”